```javascript
function appendFileRows(files) {
  var table = document.getElementById('fileTable');
  table.innerHTML = ''; // Clear the table before adding new rows

  files.forEach(function(file) {
    var row = document.createElement('tr');
    var nameCell = document.createElement('td');
    var sizeCell = document.createElement('td');
    var typeCell = document.createElement('td');

    nameCell.textContent = file.name;
    sizeCell.textContent = file.size + ' bytes';
    typeCell.textContent = file.type;

    // Set background image based on file type
    var typeIcon = 'default';
    switch (file.type) {
      case 'image/jpeg':
      case 'image/png':
      case 'image/gif':
        typeIcon = 'image';
        break;
      case 'audio/mpeg':
      case 'audio/wav':
        typeIcon = 'audio';
        break;
      case 'video/mp4':
      case 'video/webm':
        typeIcon = 'video';
        break;
      default:
        typeIcon = 'unknown';
    }
    typeCell.style.backgroundImage = 'url("icons/' + typeIcon + '.png")';

    row.appendChild(nameCell);
    row.appendChild(sizeCell);
    row.appendChild(typeCell);
    table.appendChild(row);
  });
}
```

This function takes an array of files as input, clears the existing table, and appends a new row for each file. It sets the background image of the type cell based on the file's MIME type. The function uses a switch statement to determine the appropriate icon for each file type and sets the `backgroundImage` property accordingly. The icons are assumed to be stored in a directory named "icons" with filenames like "image.png", "audio.png", "video.png", and "unknown.png". If the file type does not match any of the specified types, it defaults to the "unknown" icon. The `fileTable` should be an existing HTML table with the id "fileTable" where the rows will be appended. The `files` parameter should be an array of `File` objects obtained from a file input element. ```

